\begin_inset Formula \[
	\hat \mu_{t+1} = B \hat\mu_t + C
\]
\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $C$
\end_inset

 are both random with means 
\begin_inset Formula $\barB$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\barC$
\end_inset

, and variances 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_B^2$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_C^2$
\end_inset

 . Suppose that 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat\mu$
\end_inset

 is distributed according to the ergodic distribution of this linear system with mean 
\begin_inset Formula $\EE\hat\mu$
\end_inset

 and variance 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma^2_\mu$
\end_inset

. Since 
\begin_inset Formula \[
	B\hat\mu +C
\]
\end_inset

has the same distribution we can compute the mean of this distribution as 
\begin_inset Formula \[
\begin{split}
	\EE\hat\mu &= \EE\left[ B\hat\mu+C\right]\\
			  &= \EE\left[\EE_{\hat\mu}\left[B\hat\mu+C\right]\right]\\
			  &= \EE\left[\barB\hat\mu +\barC\right]\\
			  &=\barB\EE\hat\mu+\barC
\end{split}
\]
\end_inset

solving for 
\begin_inset Formula $\EE\hat\mu$
\end_inset

 we get 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
	\EE\hat\mu = \frac{\barC}{1-\barB}
\end{equation}
\end_inset

